					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11209243#post-4267621</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11209243/scp-4252#post-4267621</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2019 23:50:58 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RockTeethMothEyes</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4022320</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Well, that was about as weird as I imagined.</p> <p>I'm a bit hesitant to vote on this. The formatting and delivery is a bit wonky at times, with the primary designation of SCP-4252 coming in halfway through the article and the video log being a single crammed text wall in a quote block. However, it's a fun little thing you've got here. I'll admit I was a little confused by the ending, but after thinking about it for a while, it really does make sense within the logic of the skip's existence.</p> <p>All in all, I think it could be improved upon still in terms of presentation, but it isn't enough to detract from the article's contents. This is an upvote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
